{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"developer|diagnostic|inspector|debug|system\" backend/app frontend/src docs prompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "prompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:7:Add a hidden or developer-only inspector for session internals so it is easier to debug long AI-driven workflows.\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:10:- Create a developer surface that can show current session snapshot, plan revision, active jobs, recent events, and current artifact inventory.\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:16:- Developer debug inspector\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:22:- Developers can inspect what the system thinks is true without manually querying the database.\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:23:- The inspector stays out of the main user experience.\nprompts/87-developer-debug-inspector.md:32:`feat(prompt-87): developer debug inspector`\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2015:              className=\"workspace-stage-panel continuity-inspector\"\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.tsx:2046:                    <ul className=\"continuity-inspector__list\">\ndocs/storage-buckets-and-prefixes.md:16:| Sessions | `storyteller-sessions` | Partial composition drafts and debug artifacts |\ndocs/storage-buckets-and-prefixes.md:39:| Debug artifact | Sessions | `sessions/{session_id}/debug/{artifact_group}/{artifact_name}.{ext}` | `sessions/sess-42/debug/prompt-assembly/request.json` |\ndocs/storage-buckets-and-prefixes.md:77:That command writes a sample debug artifact, reads it back, and prints the resulting bucket, key,\nfrontend/src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx:3513:  it('renders the continuity bible inspector when hydrated facts are available', async () => {\nbackend/app/services/composition_prompt_assembly.py:137:            system_instructio