pe prompts and estimates, but the system should favor story quality, bedtime tone, and coherent pacing over exact numeric compliance.\ndocs/product-brief.md:56:- The system should periodically summarize what it is writing in chat.\ndocs/README.md:8:- `architecture-overview.md`: target system shape and durable boundaries\ndocs/README.md:19:- `system-diagram.md`: one-page runtime diagram for browser, API, worker, storage, and Gemini flows\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:4:The goal is to make session history durable enough for replay, resume debugging,\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:17:  - `system`: worker-owned or infrastructure-owned progress events.\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:32:| `chat.message.recorded` | User, assistant, or system chat/history entry. | varies | optional |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:34:| `composition.progress.recorded` | Durable composition job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `composition` |\ndocs/event-taxonomy.md:35:| `audio.progress.recorded` | Durable narration job progress for replay and worker debugging. | `system` | `audio` |\nfrontend/src/features/session/sessionRuntimeStore.test.ts:318:        actor_type: 'system',\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:160:The system should support these reopen flows without guessing from UI state:\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:47:That means a local developer can copy the example file, add a Gemini key, and start the full stack without exposing the key to the browser.\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:94:  enable_debug_inspector: false\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:157:            \"system\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:544:            \"system\",\ndocs/realtime-events.schema.json:1553:            \"system\",\ndocs/realtime-events.md:87:    \"actor_type\": \"system\",\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:80:  if (role === 'assistant' || role === 'user' || role === 'system') {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:84:  return 'system'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/actionEchoes.ts:403:        role: 'system',\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/SessionChatPane.test.tsx:8:    role: 'system',\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:89:The product should prefer a coherent, calm bedtime story over exact numeric compliance. If the system misses a target, it should do so transparently and gracefully rather than by truncating or padding the story unnaturally.\ndocs/adr/0001-core-runtime-architecture.md:103:- The system is more complex than a single FastAPI process with synchronous handlers.\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtime.ts:11:export type SessionEventActorType = 'user' | 'assistant' | 'system' | 'service'\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtime.ts:234:const sessionChatRoles = ['assistant', 'user', 'system', 'action_echo'] as const\nfrontend/src/features/session/live/sessionRealtime.ts:243:const actorTypes = ['user', 'assistant', 'system', 'service'] as const\nbackend/app/ai/intent_parser.py:271:                \"systemInstruction\": {\nbackend/app/settings/config.py:228:            \"enable_debug_inspector\": False,\nbackend/app/settings/config.py:293:            \"enable_debug_inspector\": _read_env_bool(\nbackend/app/settings/config.py:434:    enable_debug_inspector: bool = False\nbackend/app/ai/prompts/pitch_generation.md:7:- Keep every pitch clearly distinct from the others. Vary the story engine, inciting incident, emotional repair path, and image system.\nbackend/app/ai/character_generation.py:96:                \"systemInstruction\": {\nbackend/app/ai/beat_sheet_generation.py:96:                \"systemInstruction\": {\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/sessionChat.ts:7:  | 'system'\nfrontend/src/features/session/chat/sessionChat.ts:81:      role: 'system',\nfrontend/src/features/sessio