{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Started", "message": "in progress: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"gemini:|enable_debug_inspector|secrets.yaml\" docs/secrets-and-local-config.md secrets.example.yaml README.md backend/README.md'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"gemini:|enable_debug_inspector|secrets.yaml\" docs/secrets-and-local-config.md secrets.example.yaml README.md backend/README.md'", "exit_code": null, "id": "item_148", "status": "in_progress", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.started"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 310, "prompt_index": 59, "prompt_name": "58 \u2014 Usage, Cost, and Latency Metrics", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T05:36:40-07:00"}
{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"gemini:|enable_debug_inspector|secrets.yaml\" docs/secrets-and-local-config.md secrets.example.yaml README.md backend/README.md'", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "backend/README.md:45:cp ../secrets.example.yaml ../secrets.yaml\nbackend/README.md:48:The settings module merges built-in defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and then `STORYTELLER_*` environment variables. Environment variables win when both sources set the same field. The backend-only Gemini key lives in `secrets.yaml` or the backend process environment and is never sent to the browser.\nREADME.md:45:- Secrets handling: local `secrets.yaml`, never committed to git\nREADME.md:72:- creates `secrets.yaml` from `secrets.example.yaml` if it does not exist yet\nREADME.md:91:`secrets.yaml` is already gitignored and reserved for local-only credentials. `make bootstrap` will create it from `secrets.example.yaml` when needed, but you still need to replace the placeholder Gemini API key before using AI-backed workflows. The repo-managed Git hook blocks accidental commits of `secrets.yaml`, `.env` files, and obvious live key material. The compose file uses development defaults for Postgres and the GCS emulator, while the backend loads secrets from the repo-root `secrets.yaml` at container startup.\nREADME.md:103:- `make bootstrap`: first-run setup for hooks, local Python deps, frontend deps, and a local `secrets.yaml`\nREADME.md:153:The backend settings layer merges defaults, `secrets.yaml`, and environment variables in that order. More detail is in [docs/secrets-and-local-config.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md).\nsecrets.example.yaml:12:gemini:\nsecrets.example.yaml:35:  enable_debug_inspector: false\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:5:1. `secrets.yaml` for local-only values\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:11:2. `secrets.yaml`\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:14:Environment variables always win over `secrets.yaml`.\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:18:`secrets.yaml` is the live local credentials file. It must never be committed, copied into tracked examples, or pasted into checked-in docs. The repository keeps exactly one tracked template for that shape: `secrets.example.yaml`.\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:26:Tracked examples must contain placeholders only. Real credentials belong in local-only files such as `secrets.yaml` or in shell environment variables that stay outside git.\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:32:The backend looks for `secrets.yaml` in this order:\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:44:STORYTELLER_SECRETS_FILE=/workspace/secrets.yaml\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:54:cp secrets.example.yaml secrets.yaml\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:65:The hook blocks commits that stage `secrets.yaml`, `.env` files, or obvious Gemini/private-key material.\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:69:`secrets.yaml` uses the same nested structure as the backend settings object:\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:75:gemini:\ndocs/secrets-and-local-config.md:94:  enable_debug_inspector: false\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc 'rg -n \"gemini:|enable_debug_inspector|secrets.yaml\" docs/secrets-and-local-config.md secrets.example.yaml README.md backend/README.md'", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_148", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 311, "prompt_index": 59, "prompt_name": "58 \u2014 Usage, Cost, and Latency Metrics", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T05:36:40-07:00"}
