{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "Implemented durable model-usage telemetry and committed the code changes as `8ed00ed` (`feat(prompt-58): usage cost and latency metrics`). The backend now records per-call Gemini usage events and per-session rollups, exposes session usag...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_181", "text": "Implemented durable model-usage telemetry and committed the code changes as `8ed00ed` (`feat(prompt-58): usage cost and latency metrics`).\n\nThe backend now records per-call Gemini usage events and per-session rollups, exposes session usage summaries in hydration, and adds `GET /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/usage` for developer diagnostics. It also preserves attempted `model_id` and `prompt_version` on heuristic fallbacks so failed/discarded calls still appear in metrics. Approximate pricing is configurable under `gemini.approximate_pricing`, with lightweight local defaults documented in [secrets.example.yaml](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/secrets.example.yaml) and [docs/secrets-and-local-config.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/docs/secrets-and-local-config.md).\n\nVerification:\n- Targeted changed-file lint: passed\n- Targeted tests: `64 passed`\n- Broader touched-area tests: `37 passed`\n- Full backend suite: `208 passed, 5 skipped`\n\nNo browser or screenshot verification was needed because this prompt only changed backend/API behavior. The required reviewer summary was written as the final action to [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/58_usage_cost_and_latency_metrics/summary.md).", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 371, "prompt_index": 59, "prompt_name": "58 \u2014 Usage, Cost, and Latency Metrics", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T05:42:08-07:00"}
